      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/26/10",
      "text": [
        " «إِنْ خَرَجَ قَبْلَ أَنْ يَنْتَصِفَ اَلنَّهَارُ فَلْيُفْطِرْ وَ لْيَقْضِ ذَلِكَ اَلْيَوْمَ وَ إِنْ خَرَجَ بَعْدَ اَلزَّوَالِ فَلْيُتِمَّ يَوْمَهُ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1982 - Al-Halabi narrated from Imam Abu Abdullah (as):\nHe was asked about a man who leaves his house intending to travel while fasting.\nThe Imam (as) replied: \"If he departs before the middle of the day, let him break his fast and make up that day. But if he departs after midday, let him complete his day.\""
        ]
      }
